Nobel Peace Prize and indigenous activist [Rigoberta
Menchú](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rigoberta_Menchu) will be nominated as
the Frente Amplio de Izquierda presidential candidate, according to [recent
reports](http://www.prensalibre.com/elecciones_2011/Frente-Amplio-confirma-
Menchu-precandidata_0_473353021.html) [es]. Mike in [_Central American
Politics_](http://centralamericanpolitics.blogspot.com/2011/05/president-
rigoberta-menchu.html) thinks that “even with the rejuvenated Guatemalan left,
it's unlikely that Manchu (or any other left candidate) will impact the
outcome of the presidential elections.”

